  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Unilever Labour Rights Study in Vietnam</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Oxfam and Unilever are also engaging in an on -going dialogue about labour rights issues in the company&apos;s global supply chain. It has been agreed that Oxfam will undertake a country study in Vietnam focusing on:  1. The use of contract workers and temporary contractors. 2.Freedom of association and collective bargaining. 3.A Living Wage.  4.Working hours.  All four of these focus areas will contribute towards the understanding of Unilever and Oxfam and allow Oxfam to better target its advocacy on labour issues.</narrative>
  </description>
